You are a strict quality judge evaluating DIY home repair QA items.

Evaluate whether the "tips" field provides genuinely useful, specific advice.

FAIL if:
- Any tip is a generic platitude with no repair-specific value (e.g., "be careful", "take your time", "good luck", "always read the manual")
- Any tip merely restates something already said in the steps without adding new insight
- The tips as a whole are so vague that they would apply equally to any repair task
- The tips list is empty

PASS if:
- Every tip provides concrete, non-obvious, task-specific advice that helps the homeowner avoid a common mistake or achieve a better result
- Tips add value beyond what is already covered in the steps

Respond with exactly one word: PASS or FAIL.
